  'amaranth-greens', 'FMT-TH-BL', 'Amaranth Greens', 'Traditional Herbs', 'Amaranthus spp.',
  'InStock', 'Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried', '["amaranth greens wildcrafted","amaranthus spp dried","bledo tea","amaranth greens herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","amaranth greens traditional uses","amaranth greens healthy skin","amaranth greens digestive health","amaranthus spp benefits"]', '["bledo","amaranthus leaves","quelite","pigweed"]', 'Shade-dried Amaranthus leaves, known as bledo, rooted in Mesoamerican food tradition for skin vitality and whole-body nourishment.',
  '{"handler":"amaranth-greens","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-BL","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Amaranth Greens","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":21,"botanical":"Amaranthus spp.","material":"whole plant","ingredients":"Shade-dried amaranth leaves, naturally rich in minerals, amino acids, and antioxidants.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Shade-dried Amaranthus leaves, known as bledo, rooted in Mesoamerican food tradition for skin vitality and whole-body nourishment.","description":"The vibrant leaves of Amaranthus spp., known as ''bledo'' in Honduran tradition, represent a sacred legacy of Mesoamerican nourishment. Hand-gathered from wild fields, these greens carry the ancestral wisdom of indigenous harvesters who have valued them for generations. \n\nCelebrated for their vitality-sustaining properties and deep cultural roots, they are carefully dried to preserve their nutritional power. Offered in whole-leaf form, free from modern processing or contaminants.","commonNames":["bledo","amaranthus leaves","quelite","pigweed"],"traditionalUses":["Promotes healthy skin","Supports digestive health","Helps cells protection","Soothes bones and muscles"],"howToUse":["Culinary Preparation (Cooked Greens): Thoroughly wash Amaranth greens and remove tough lower stems, keeping only tender leaves and upper stems. Bring a large pot of salted water to a rolling boil. Add Amaranth greens and boil for 2-5 minutes until tender but still bright green. Drain immediately in a colander. Serve warm, drizzled with extra virgin olive oil, fresh lemon juice, and sea salt.","Sautéed Preparation: After blanching (as above), heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add chopped onion and garlic, sauté until fragrant. Add blanched Amaranth greens, stir-fry for 2-3 minutes. Season with salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lemon. Serve warm as a nutritious side dish.","In Soups & Stews: Add fresh Amaranth greens directly to soups, stews, or curries during the last 5-10 minutes of cooking. The greens will wilt and add nutritious depth to your dish.","Nutritional Tea (Mild Infusion): Place a handful of fresh Amaranth greens in boiling water for 2-3 minutes. Strain and drink the mild green infusion for its mineral and vitamin content.","Nutritional Benefits: Amaranth greens are exceptionally rich in iron, calcium, vitamins A, C, and K, protein, and fiber—making them one of the most nutritious leafy greens available."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["amaranth greens wildcrafted","amaranthus spp dried","bledo tea","amaranth greens herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","amaranth greens traditional uses","amaranth greens healthy skin","amaranth greens digestive health","amaranthus spp benefits"],"relatedProducts":["moringa-leaves","nettle-leaves","guava-leaves","hibiscus-flowers","soursop-leaves"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"amaranth-greens","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-BL","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/amaranth-greens.png","alt":"Amaranth Greens - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Amaranth Greens — Shade-Dried Bledo from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/amaranth-greens.png","alt":"Pile of dried dark green amaranth greens on white background","caption":"Wildcrafted amaranth greens from Honduras - finely cut dried leaves for traditional herbal preparations","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-bl-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/amaranth-greens-57-g.png","alt":"Amaranth Greens 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Amaranth Greens - Bledo - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-bl-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/amaranth-greens-113-g.png","alt":"Amaranth Greens 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Amaranth Greens - Bledo - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-bl-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/amaranth-greens-454-g.png","alt":"Amaranth Greens 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Amaranth Greens - Bledo - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"}]}', '{"handler":"amaranth-greens","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","productSlug":"amaranth-greens","seoTitle":"Amaranth Greens | Bledo Wildcrafted Amaranthus Leafy","seoDescription":"Wild-gathered Amaranthus leaves from Honduran fields. A sacred Mesoamerican superfood, dried to preserve its nutritional power.","ogImageUrl":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/amaranth-greens.png","ogImageAlt":"Pile of dried dark green amaranth greens on white background","ogImageCaption":"Wildcrafted amaranth greens from Honduras - finely cut dried leaves for traditional herbal preparations","ogImageWidth":1200,"ogImageHeight":630,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","relatedProducts":"moringa-leaves, nettle-leaves, guava-leaves, hibiscus-flowers, soursop-leaves","published":true}'
