  '{"handler":"blessed-holy-thistle","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-HT","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Blessed - Holy Thistle","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":9,"botanical":"Cnicus benedictus","material":"whole plant","ingredients":"Shade-dried holy thistle, traditionally used for digestion and wellness.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Cardo Santo (Cnicus benedictus), shade-dried and rooted in sacred herbal tradition, valued for digestive balance, appetite support, and lactation wellness.","description":"The thorny leaves of Cnicus benedictus, known as ''cardo santo'' or ''blessed thistle,'' have journeyed from Mediterranean monasteries to Honduras'' highland gardens as a plant of sacred herbalism. Wild-harvested from naturalized stands, these leaves carry centuries of European and adapted Central American knowledge about bitter tonics and traditional wellness. \n\nRevered for their protective spines and time-honored digestive applications, they are shade-dried to preserve their sesquiterpene lactone content. Offered chopped, free from pesticides or monastery garden romanticism that obscures botanical reality.","commonNames":["Cardo Santo","Cardo Bendito"],"traditionalUses":["Helps support lactation","Assists with skin health","Promotes appetite","Stimulates digestive secretions"],"howToUse":["Herbal Infusion (Tea): Measure 1-3 teaspoons (1.5-3g) of dried Blessed Thistle herb into a teacup or teapot. Pour 1 cup (240ml) of boiling water over the herb. Cover and steep for 5-10 minutes. Strain and drink 2 cups daily, preferably 30 minutes to 1 hour before meals for digestive support.","For Digestive Health & Appetite Stimulation: Drink 1 c