  '{"handler":"cassia-pods","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-CF","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Cassia Pods","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":10,"botanical":"Cassia fistula","material":"sticks","ingredients":"Shade-dried cassia pods, known for their gentle cleansing plant compounds.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Shade-dried Golden Shower Tree pods (Cassia fistula), or caña fístula, rooted in Honduran tradition for digestion and natural cleansing support.","description":"The distinctive seed pods of Cassia fistula, known locally as ''caña fístula,'' dangle like natural medicine cabinets from Honduras'' tropical canopies. Wild-harvested at peak maturity, these pods carry centuries of indigenous knowledge about gentle yet effective traditional wellness practices. \n\nRevered for their time-honored uses and subtle potency, they are carefully dried to preserve their inner pulp and seeds. Offered whole, allowing traditional preparation methods to unlock their ancestral benefits, free from chemical treatment or artificial processing.","commonNames":["Caña Fístula","Golden Shower Tree"],"traditionalUses":["Digestive cleansing","Bolsters natural defenses","Throat and respiratory soothing","Supports urinary tract"],"howToUse":["Herbal Tea (Pod Pieces): Break 2-3 Cassia pod segments (approximately 5-10cm total length) into smaller pieces. Place in a pot with 2-3 cups (500-750ml) of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20-30 minutes until water turns golden-brown. Strain and drink 1 cup 1-2 times daily.","For Gentle Digestive Support: Drink 1 cup of Cassia pod tea in the morning or evening to support healthy bowel movements and di