  '{"handler":"hibiscus-flowers","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-HF","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Hibiscus Flowers","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":22,"botanical":"Hibiscus sabdariffa","material":"flowers","ingredients":"Shade-dried hibiscus flowers, naturally rich in vitamin C and antioxidants.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Wild-harvested Flor de Jamaica (Hibiscus sabdariffa), cherished in Mesoamerican tradition for cooling infusions, heartful refreshment, and vibrant wellness.","description":"The crimson calyces of Hibiscus sabdariffa, beloved as ''flor de Jamaica'' or ''rosa de Jamaica,'' paint Honduran markets and traditional beverages with their tart, ruby essence. Wild-harvested from native plantings, these flowers carry generations of Mesoamerican knowledge about refreshment, vitality, and celebratory wellness. \n\nCelebrated for their vibrant color and cooling properties, they are shade-dried to preserve their anthocyanin-rich profile and natural acidity. Offered whole, ready for traditional infusion or culinary use, free from artificial colorants or sweeteners.","commonNames":["Flor de Lamaica"],"traditionalUses":["Supports blood pressure levels","Helps maintain normal cholesterol levels","Provides antioxidant support","Contributes to liver health"],"howToUse":["Hibiscus Tea (Hot Preparation): Place 1-2 tablespoons (approximately 5-10g) of dried Hibiscus flowers in a teapot. Pour 1 cup (240ml) of boiling water over the flowers. Cover and steep for 5-10 minutes until the water turns deep ruby red. Strain and sweeten with honey or agave if desired. Drink hot or warm.","Agua de Jamaica (Cold Preparation): Combine 1/4 cup (appro