  '{"handler":"lemongrass","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-LG","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Lemongrass","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":25,"botanical":"Cymbopogon citratus","material":"leaves","ingredients":"Shade-dried lemongrass, rich in naturally calming plant oils.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Shade-dried Lemongrass (Cymbopogon citratus), known as zacate de limón, traditionally enjoyed for digestive comfort, calm, and refreshing vitality.","description":"The aromatic stalks and leaves of Cymbopogon citratus, called ''zacate de limón'' or ''té de limón,'' perfume Honduras'' tropical gardens and wild margins with their bright citral essence. Hand-cut from naturalized stands, these grasses carry generations of Southeast Asian and adapted Central American knowledge about digestive comfort and aromatic healing. \n\nCelebrated for their refreshing flavor and versatile applications in both wellness and culinary traditions, they are shade-dried to preserve their essential oil profile. Offered chopped or whole, free from synthetic citral or artificial lemon flavoring.","commonNames":["Zacate de limon","citronella"],"traditionalUses":["Promotes digestive comfort","Assists relaxation and calm","Supports healthy microbial balance","Provides antioxidant defense"],"howToUse":["Lemongrass Tea (Fresh or Dried): If using fresh Lemongrass, take 2-3 stalks (approximately 15-20cm length), remove tough outer layers, and cut into 2-3 cm pieces. Bruise or twist the pieces to release oils. If using dried Lemongrass, use 1-2 teaspoons (3-5g). Place in a pot with 2 cups (500ml) of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5-10 minutes. Stra