  'moringa-leaves', 'FMT-TH-MO', 'Moringa Leaves', 'Traditional Herbs', 'Moringa oleifera',
  'OutOfStock', 'Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried', '["moringa leaves wildcrafted","moringa oleifera dried","hojas de moringa tea","moringa leaves herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","moringa leaves traditional uses","moringa leaves comprehensive nutritional support","moringa leaves healthy blood sugar levels","moringa oleifera benefits"]', '["hojas de moringa"]', 'Moringa oleifera, known as the miracle tree, shade-dried and traditionally valued for iron vitality, lactation support, and whole-body nourishment.',
  '{"handler":"moringa-leaves","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-MO","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Moringa Leaves","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":28,"botanical":"Moringa oleifera","material":"leaves","ingredients":"Shade-dried moringa leaves, naturally rich in vitamins, minerals, and plant proteins.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Moringa oleifera, known as the miracle tree, shade-dried and traditionally valued for iron vitality, lactation support, and whole-body nourishment.","description":"The pinnate leaves of Moringa oleifera, celebrated as ''árbol de la vida'' or ''miracle tree,'' cascade from branches that have fed communities across Africa, Asia, and now Central America. Wild-harvested from Honduras'' naturalized groves, these leaves carry profound nutritional wisdom recognized by indigenous healers and modern nutritionists alike. \n\nRevered as one of nature''s most complete plant foods, they are shade-dried immediately after harvest to lock in their exceptional vitamin, mineral, and protein density. Offered in whole leaves or powder form, free from heat degradation or nutrient-stripping processing.","commonNames":["hojas de moringa"],"traditionalUses":["Provides comprehensive nutritional support","Supports healthy blood sugar levels","Promotes antioxidant defense","Aids energy and vitality"],"howToUse":["Moringa Leaf Tea: Place 1 teaspoon (approximately 3-5g) of dried Moringa leaves in a teapot or cup. Pour 1 cup (240ml) of freshly boiled water (95-100°C) over the leaves. Cover and steep for 3-5 minutes. Do not oversteep, as Moringa can become bitter. Strain and drink 2-3 cups daily.","Moringa Powder (In Beverages): Add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon of Moringa leaf powder to smoothies, juices, or lukewarm water (not hot, to preserve nutrients). Stir well and consume immediately. Take 1-2 times daily.","For Nutritional Support & Energy: Drink 1-2 cups of Moringa tea daily or add powder to morning smoothies for exceptional nutritional density. Moringa is one of the most nutrient-rich plants on earth, providing vitamins A, C, E, calcium, potassium, protein, and antioxidants.","For Blood Sugar Balance: Consume Moringa tea or powder consistently, 2-3 times daily, to traditionally support healthy blood sugar metabolism.","For Lactation Support (Traditional Use): Nursing mothers may drink 2-3 cups of Moringa tea daily to traditionally support milk production."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["moringa leaves wildcrafted","moringa oleifera dried","hojas de moringa tea","moringa leaves herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","moringa leaves traditional uses","moringa leaves comprehensive nutritional support","moringa leaves healthy blood sugar levels","moringa oleifera benefits"],"relatedProducts":["nettle-leaves","amaranth-greens","hibiscus-flowers","soursop-leaves","guava-leaves"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"moringa-leaves","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-MO","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/moringa-leaves.png","alt":"Moringa Leaves - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Moringa Leaves — Shade-Dried Hojas de Moringa from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/moringa-leaves.png","alt":"Large pile of bright green dried moringa leaf pieces showing nutrient-rich quality","caption":"Moringa Leaves from Honduras - premium dried Moringa oleifera leaves rich in vitamins and minerals","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-mo-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/moringa-leaves-57-g.png","alt":"Moringa Leaves 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Moringa Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-mo-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/moringa-leaves-113-g.png","alt":"Moringa Leaves 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Moringa Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-mo-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/moringa-leaves-454-g.png","alt":"Moringa Leaves 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Moringa Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"}]}', '{"handler":"moringa-leaves","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","productSlug":"moringa-leaves","seoTitle":"Moringa Leaves | Miracle Tree Moringa Oleifera Honduras","seoDescription":"Wild-harvested Moringa oleifera leaves from Honduras. One of nature''s most complete plant foods, rich in vitamins and protein.","ogImageUrl":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/moringa-leaves.png","ogImageAlt":"Large pile of bright green dried moringa leaf pieces showing nutrient-rich quality","ogImageCaption":"Moringa Leaves from Honduras - premium dried Moringa oleifera leaves rich in vitamins and minerals","ogImageWidth":1200,"ogImageHeight":630,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","relatedProducts":"nettle-leaves, amaranth-greens, hibiscus-flowers, soursop-leaves, guava-leaves","published":true}'
