  '{"handler":"neem-leaves","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-NM","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Neem Leaves","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":30,"botanical":"Azadirachta indica","material":"leaves","ingredients":"Shade-dried neem leaves, known for their naturally bitter and protective plant compounds.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Neem (Azadirachta indica), known in Ayurveda as the village pharmacy, shade-dried and valued for skin vitality, natural defense, and cleansing support.","description":"The bitter, pinnate leaves of Azadirachta indica, called ''nim'' across Honduras'' tropical lowlands, have journeyed from Indian Ayurvedic tradition to become guardians of Central American wellness. Wild-harvested from naturalized trees, these leaves carry millennia of South Asian knowledge about purification, protection, and microbial balance. \n\nRevered for their powerful cleansing properties and traditional applications in skin and oral care, they are shade-dried to preserve their limonoid and azadirachtin content. Offered whole or crushed, free from synthetic antimicrobials or chemical pest treatments.","commonNames":["hojas de neem"],"traditionalUses":["Supports healthy microbial balance","Promotes skin and scalp health","Aids oral hygiene maintenance","Provides natural cleansing properties"],"howToUse":["Neem Leaf Tea (Mild Preparation): Place 3-5 whole dried Neem leaves (or 1/4 teaspoon of Neem leaf powder) in a cup. Pour 1 cup (240ml) of warm (not boiling) water over the leaves. Allow to steep for 3-5 minutes. Strain and sweeten with honey to offset bitterness. Drink 1-2 cups daily, preferably in the morning on an empty stomach.","For Immune Support & Detoxification: Drink 1 cup of Neem tea daily, ideally first thing in the morning, to support immune function, promote gentle detoxification, and maintain overall wellness. Traditional use suggests weekly or periodic consumption rather than daily long-term use.","For Skin Health (Internal & Topical): Consume Neem tea internally for skin wellness from within. For external use, prepare a strong Neem tea and apply topically to affected skin areas for traditional support of healthy skin.","For Blood Sugar Support: Drink 1 cup of Neem tea before breakfast to traditionally support healthy blood sugar metabolism.","Taste Note: Neem is intensely bitter. Blend with honey, cinnamon, orange peel, or black tea to improve palatability. Start with weaker concentrations and increase gradually."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["neem leaves wildcrafted","azadirachta indica dried","hojas de neem tea","neem leaves herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","neem leaves traditional uses","neem leaves healthy microbial balance","neem leaves skin and scalp health","azadirachta indica benefits"],"relatedProducts":["plantain-leaf","gumbo-limbo-leaves","kalawalla-root","leaf-of-life-miracle-leaf","sensitive-plant"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"neem-leaves","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-NM","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/neem-leaves.png","alt":"Neem Leaves - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Neem Leaves — Shade-Dried Hojas de Neem from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/neem-leaves.png","alt":"Dried neem leaves showing characteristic compound leaf structure and green color","caption":"Neem Leaves from Honduras - Azadirachta indica leaves with traditional wellness applications","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-nm-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/neem-leaves-57-g.png","alt":"Neem Leaves 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Neem Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-nm-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/neem-leaves-113-g.png","alt":"Neem Leaves 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Neem Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-nm-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/neem-leaves-454-g.png","alt":"Neem Leaves 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Neem Leaves - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"}]}',