  'palo-guaco', 'FMT-TH-PG', 'Palo Guaco', 'Traditional Herbs', 'Mikania spp.',
  'InStock', 'Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried', '["palo guaco wildcrafted","mikania spp dried","guaco tea","palo guaco herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","palo guaco traditional uses","palo guaco respiratory function and clear breathing","palo guaco mucus clearance","mikania spp benefits"]', '["Guaco"]', 'Wildcrafted Palo Guaco vine (Mikania spp), rooted in Central American tradition for respiratory comfort, soothing warmth, and natural ease.',
  '{"handler":"palo-guaco","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-PG","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Palo Guaco","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":32,"botanical":"Mikania spp.","material":"stem","ingredients":"Shade-dried mikania leaves, traditionally used for comfort and relief.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Wildcrafted Palo Guaco vine (Mikania spp), rooted in Central American tradition for respiratory comfort, soothing warmth, and natural ease.","description":"The aromatic wood and bark of Mikania species, known as ''palo guaco,'' embody Central American respiratory tradition in woody, climbing form. Wild-harvested from Honduras'' humid forest margins where the vine ascends into canopy light, this wood carries generations of indigenous wisdom about breath, seasonal wellness, and lung support. \n\nRevered for its powerful volatile compounds and time-honored applications in respiratory care, it is carefully processed to preserve its coumarin-rich profile. Offered in wood pieces or chips, free from synthetic expectorants or pharmaceutical modification.","commonNames":["Guaco"],"traditionalUses":["Supports respiratory function and clear breathing","Promotes mucus clearance","Bolsters immune system defenses","Boosts inflammatory response"],"howToUse":["Note: Palo Guaco (stem) is prepared similarly to Guaco leaves but uses the woody stem pieces.","Herbal Decoction (Stem Preparation): Place 10-15g of Palo Guaco stem pieces in a pot with 2-3 cups (500-750ml) of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes. Remove from heat, cover, and steep for an additional 10 minutes. Strain and drink 1-2 cups 2-3 times daily.","For Respiratory Health & Cough: Drink 1 cup of Palo Guaco decoction 2-3 times daily to traditionally support bronchial health, ease persistent cough, and help clear respiratory passages.","For Asthma & Bronchitis Support: Consume Palo Guaco tea consistently, 3 times daily during respiratory challenges. The natural bronchodilatory properties provide traditional relief.","Traditional Note: Palo Guaco stem is considered more concentrated than the leaves and is used when stronger respiratory support is needed."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["palo guaco wildcrafted","mikania spp dried","guaco tea","palo guaco herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","palo guaco traditional uses","palo guaco respiratory function and clear breathing","palo guaco mucus clearance","mikania spp benefits"],"relatedProducts":["guaco-leaves","eucalyptus-leaves","trumpet-tree-leaves","pine-needles","palo-santo"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"palo-guaco","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-PG","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/palo-guaco.png","alt":"Palo Guaco - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Palo Guaco — Wildcrafted Mikania Vine from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/palo-guaco.png","alt":"Dried palo guaco bark and wood pieces showing natural brown woody texture","caption":"Palo Guaco from Honduras - traditional bark and wood used in Central American wellness practices","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-pg-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/palo-guaco-57-g.png","alt":"Palo Guaco 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Palo Guaco - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pg-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/palo-guaco-113-g.png","alt":"Palo Guaco 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Palo Guaco - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pg-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/palo-guaco-454-g.png","alt":"Palo Guaco 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Palo Guaco - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"}]}', '{"handler":"palo-guaco","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","productSlug":"palo-guaco","seoTitle":"Palo Guaco | Wild Mikania from Honduras Forests","seoDescription":"Wild-harvested Mikania wood from Honduras'' humid forests. A coumarin-rich traditional herb for respiratory care and seasonal wellness.","ogImageUrl":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/palo-guaco.png","ogImageAlt":"Dried palo guaco bark and wood pieces showing natural brown woody texture","ogImageCaption":"Palo Guaco from Honduras - traditional bark and wood used in Central American wellness practices","ogImageWidth":1200,"ogImageHeight":630,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","relatedProducts":"guaco-leaves, eucalyptus-leaves, trumpet-tree-leaves, pine-needles, palo-santo","published":true}'
