  '{"handler":"pine-needles","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-PN","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Pine Needles","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":35,"botanical":"Pinus spp.","material":"leaves","ingredients":"Shade-dried pine needles, naturally aromatic and rich in plant-based vitamin C.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Pinus oocarpa needles from Honduran highlands, shade-dried and traditionally brewed for breath comfort, natural vitality, and circulatory warmth.","description":"The slender, resinous needles of Pinus species, known simply as ''hojas de pino,'' bristle from Honduras'' highland forests with their sharp, turpentine essence. Hand-picked from native and naturalized pines, these needles carry North American indigenous and adapted Central American knowledge about respiratory clarity and vitamin C sufficiency. \n\nRevered for their high pinene content and traditional applications in seasonal wellness, they are shade-dried to preserve their volatile oil profile and ascorbic acid. Offered whole or coarsely cut, free from industrial pine scent additives or synthetic fragrance.","commonNames":["Hojas de pino"],"traditionalUses":["Supports respiratory health and comfort","Provides antioxidant and immune support","Promotes joint and muscular comfort","Enhances energy and vitality"],"howToUse":["Pine Needle Infusion (Tea): Gather approximately 1 tablespoon (5-10g) of fresh Pine needles or 2 teaspoons of dried needles. Chop or cut into smaller pieces to release beneficial compounds. Place in a teapot and pour 1-2 cups (250-500ml) of hot water (not boiling—around 80-85°C) over the needles. Cover and steep for 10-15 minutes. Strain and drink 1-2 cups daily.","For Respiratory Support & Immunity: Drink 1-2 cups of Pine needle tea daily to support respiratory wellness, boost immune function, and provide high vitamin C content. Traditional use for cold and flu prevention.","For Antioxidant Support: Consume Pine needle tea regularly for its rich antioxidant content, including flavonoids and vitamin C, which support cellular health and overall vitality.","Pine Needle Steam (For Congestion): Place a handful of fresh Pine needles in a bowl of very hot water. Drape a towel over your head and inhale the aromatic steam for 5-10 minutes to clear sinus congestion and support respiratory comfort.","Caution: Ensure proper identification of Pine species. Avoid Ponderosa Pine, Norfolk Island Pine, and Yew, which can be toxic. Use only edible Pine species."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["pine needles wildcrafted","pinus oocarpa dried","hojas de pino tea","pine needles herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","pine needles traditional uses","pine needles respiratory health and comfort","pine needles antioxidant and immune support","pinus oocarpa benefits"],"relatedProducts":["eucalyptus-leaves","palo-guaco","thuja-cedar-leaves","guaco-leaves","palo-santo"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"pine-needles","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-PN","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/pine-needles.png","alt":"Pine Needles - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Pine Needles — Shade-Dried Pinus Oocarpa from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/pine-needles.png","alt":"Dried pine needles showing natural green color and characteristic needle structure","caption":"Pine Needles from Honduras - wildcrafted needles rich in vitamin C and natural antioxidants","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-pn-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/pine-needles-57-g.png","alt":"Pine Needles 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Pine Needles - Hojas de Pino - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pn-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/pine-needles-113-g.png","alt":"Pine Needles 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Pine Needles - Hojas de Pino - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pn-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/pine-needles-454-g.png","alt":"Pine Needles 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Pine Needles - Hojas de Pino - Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Foresta