rties provide gentle, coating relief.","For Digestive Wellness: Consume 1 cup of Plantain tea before meals to support digestive comfort, soothe stomach irritation, and promote intestinal health.","Topical Application (For Wound Healing): Crush fresh Plantain leaves to release juices and apply directly to minor cuts, scrapes, insect bites, or skin irritations. The natural astringent and antimicrobial properties support wound healing. Alternatively, prepare a strong Plantain tea, cool it, and apply as a compress to affected areas.","Poultice (For Insect Bites & Stings): Chew fresh Plantain leaves (if wild and clean) or crush thoroughly to release juices. Apply directly to insect bites or stings for immediate traditional relief from pain and swelling."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["plantain leaf wildcrafted","plantago major dried","llantén tea","plantain leaf herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","plantain leaf traditional uses","plantain leaf skin repair and soothes irritation","plantain leaf respiratory comfort","plantago major benefits"],"relatedProducts":["neem-leaves","gumbo-limbo-leaves","leaf-of-life-miracle-leaf","sensitive-plant","cows-foot-leaves"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"plantain-leaf","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-PL","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/plantain-leaf.png","alt":"Plantain Leaf - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Plantain Leaf — Shade-Dried Llantén from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/plantain-leaf.png","alt":"Dried plantain leaves showing broad leaf structure and natural green color","caption":"Plantain Leaf from Honduras - Plantago major leaves traditionally used for topical and internal wellness","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-pl-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/plantain-leaf-57-g.png","alt":"Plantain Leaf 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Plantain Leaf - Llantén - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pl-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/plantain-leaf-113-g.png","alt":"Plantain Leaf 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Plantain Leaf - Llantén - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-pl-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/plantain-leaf-454-g.png","alt":"Plantain Leaf 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Plantain Leaf - Llantén - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02