  '{"handler":"quassia-bitter-wood","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-HG","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Quassia - Bitter Wood","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":38,"botanical":"Quassia amara","material":"wood","ingredients":"Shade-dried bitterwood, known for its naturally bitter plant compounds.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Palo amargo (Quassia amara), known as hombre grande, an intensely bitter wood rooted in Central American tradition for cleansing and digestive vigor.","description":"The intensely bitter wood of Quassia amara, known locally as ''hombre grande'' or ''cruceta,'' stands as one of nature''s most powerfully flavored botanical teachers. Wild-harvested from Honduras'' tropical forests, these wood chips carry indigenous wisdom about the medicinal value of profound bitterness and traditional digestive applications. \n\nRevered for their uncompromising taste and respected place in Central American herbalism, they are processed to preserve their quassinoid compounds. Offered in wood chips or shavings, free from sweetening agents or taste modification.","commonNames":["Hombre grande","Palo amargo","Cuasia"],"traditionalUses":["Promotes digestive wellness","Supports healthy appetite","Aids scalp and hair health","Provides natural cleansing properties"],"howToUse":["Quassia Wood Infusion (Cold Soak - Traditional): Place 2-3 pieces (approximately 10-15g) of Quassia wood chips in a glass or jar with 2 cups (500ml) of cold water. Cover and let soak overnight (8-12 hours). Strain and drink 1/4 to 1/2 cup 2-3 times daily before meals. The cold infusion extracts the bitter compounds without excessive bitterness.","Hot Decoction (Alternative Method): Place Quassia wood chips in a pot with water and simmer gently for 10-15 minutes. Strain and cool. Drink in small amounts (1/4 cup) before meals.","For Digestive Support & Appetite Stimulation: Consume 1/4 cup of Quassia infusion 15-30 minutes before meals to stimulate digestive secretions, support healthy appetite, and promote proper digestion. The intense bitterness activates digestive function.","For Parasite Cleansing (Traditional Use): Drink 1/2 cup of Quassia infusion 2-3 times daily as part of a traditional parasite cleansing protocol. Use for 7-10 days.","External Use (Insect Repellent): Quassia infusion can be applied topically as a natural insect repellent or used as a hair rinse to deter lice."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["quassia - bitter wood wildcrafted","quassia amara dried","hombre grande tea","quassia - bitter wood herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","quassia - bitter wood traditional uses","quassia - bitter wood digestive wellness","quassia - bitter wood healthy appetite","quassia amara benefits"],"relatedProducts":["bitter-melon-cundeamor","stonebreaker","blessed-holy-thistle","cassia-pods","duck-flower"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"quassia-bitter-wood","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-HG","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/quassia-bitter-wood.png","alt":"Quassia - Bitter Wood - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Quassia Bitter Wood — Wildcrafted Palo Amargo from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/quassia-bitter-wood.png","alt":"Dried quassia wood chips showing pale yellowish color and characteristic bitter wood texture","caption":"Quassia Bitter Wood from Honduras - Quassia amara wood chips known for intense bitter properties","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-hg-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/quassia-bitter-wood-57-g.png","alt":"Quassia - Bitter Wood 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Quassia - Bitter Wood - Hombre Grande - Wildcrafted - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-hg-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/quassia-bitter-wood-113-g.png","alt":"Quassia - Bitter Wood 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Quassia - Bitter Wood - Hombre Grande - Wildcrafted - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-hg-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/quassia-bitter-wood-454-g.png","alt":"Quassia - Bitter Wood 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Quassia - Bitter Wood - Hombre Grande - Wildcrafted - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"ima