  '{"handler":"sarsaparilla","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-SR","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Sarsaparilla","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":39,"botanical":"Smilax spp.","material":"roots","ingredients":"Shade-dried sarsaparilla roots, known for natural cleansing and supportive plant compounds.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Zarzaparrilla root (Smilax spp), the classic Caribbean blood cleanser, wild-harvested and traditionally valued for skin vitality and deep renewal.","description":"The woody roots of Smilax species, known as ''zarzaparrilla'' or ''sarsaparilla,'' burrow through Honduras'' tropical forests as the original botanical that flavored traditional root beers and tonics. Wild-harvested with respect for the vine''s extensive underground network, these roots carry indigenous American knowledge about blood purification, vitality, and endurance. \n\nRevered for their saponin content and traditional applications in skin clarity and energy support, they are carefully processed to preserve their dense, fibrous character. Offered in cut root pieces, free from artificial sarsaparilla flavoring or synthetic saponins.","commonNames":["zarzaparrilla"],"traditionalUses":["Supports healthy circulation","Promotes clear skin appearance","Aids detoxification processes","Assists with energy and endurance"],"howToUse":["Note: Sarsaparilla (Smilax) roots are the same botanical family as Cocolmeca. Preparation methods are similar.","Strong Decoction (Root Preparation): Take a generous handful (approximately 30-40g) of Sarsaparilla root pieces and place in a large pot with half a gallon (approximately 2 liters) of water. Bring to a rolling boil, then reduce heat and simmer vigorously for 20-30 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to steep for an additional 10-20 minutes. Strain the liquid, pressing down on root pieces. Drink 2-3 cups daily.","For Blood Purification & Detoxification: Consume 2-3 cups of Sarsaparilla decoction daily for 7-14 days as part of a traditional blood cleansing protocol. The root traditionally supports lymphatic drainage and blood purification.","For Skin Health: Drink Sarsaparilla tea consistently, 2-3 cups daily, to traditionally support clear, healthy skin from within. Traditional use for eczema, psoriasis, and acne.","For Hormonal Balance: Consume Sarsaparilla decoction regularly to traditionally support hormonal balance and vitality. Traditional use as a tonic and adaptogen."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["sarsaparilla wildcrafted","smilax spp dried","zarzaparrilla tea","sarsaparilla herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","sarsaparilla traditional uses","sarsaparilla healthy circulation","sarsaparilla clear skin appearance","smilax spp benefits"],"relatedProducts":["cats-claw","cocolmeca-root","contribo","pau-darco-bark","possum-grape-cissus"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"sarsaparilla","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-SR","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/sarsaparilla.png","alt":"Sarsaparilla - Forestal MT product image","caption":"Sarsaparilla — Wild-Harvested Zarzaparrilla Root from Honduras","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"ogImage":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/og/sarsaparilla.png","alt":"Dried sarsaparilla root pieces showing dark reddish-brown color and fibrous root texture","caption":"Sarsaparilla Root from Honduras - traditional Smilax ornata root used in Central American wellness preparations","width":1200,"height":630,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},"variantImages":[{"sku":"fmt-th-sr-57-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/sarsaparilla-57-g.png","alt":"Sarsaparilla 57 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Sarsaparilla - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 57 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-sr-113-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/sarsaparilla-113-g.png","alt":"Sarsaparilla 113 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Sarsaparilla - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 113 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"},{"sku":"fmt-th-sr-454-g","url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/variants/sarsaparilla-454-g.png","alt":"Sarsaparilla 454 g - Forestal MT","caption":"Sarsaparilla - Wildcrafted in Honduras - 454 g","width":1200,"height":1200,"encodingFormat":"image/png","creator":"Forestal Murillo Tejada S. de R.L.","uploadedDate":"2026-02-16"}]}', '{"handler":"sarsaparilla",