  '{"handler":"sensitive-plant","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-DO","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","category":"Food, Beverages & Tobacco > Beverages > Tea & Infusions","brand":"Forestal MT","name":"Sensitive Plant","qualityBadge":"Wildcrafted & Shade-Dried","item":40,"botanical":"Mimosa pudica","material":"whole plant","ingredients":"Shade-dried sensitive plant leaves and roots, used for calming and soothing purposes.","origin":"Made in Honduras","storage":"Store in a cool, dry, and dark place. Always keep tightly sealed. Avoid prolonged heat and humidity.","shelfLife":"For best potency, use within 12–18 months.","shipping":"Worldwide via DHL Express","shortDescription":"Dormilona (Mimosa pudica), a touch-responsive plant rooted in tropical tradition for internal cleansing and feminine balance.","description":"The responsive leaves of Mimosa pudica, known locally as ''dormilona'' or ''vergonzosa,'' demonstrate nature''s awareness through their touch-sensitive folding. Hand-gathered from Honduras'' wild meadows and forest edges, this plant carries indigenous wisdom about sensitivity, protection, and traditional wellness applications. \n\nCelebrated for its unique behavior and ancestral uses, it is shade-dried to maintain the delicate leaflets and stems. Offered chopped for traditional preparation, free from pesticides or chemical interference with its natural properties.","commonNames":["dormilona"],"traditionalUses":["Promotes relaxation and calm","Supports nervous system wellness","Aids stress management","Provides gentle soothing properties"],"howToUse":["Herbal Infusion (Whole Plant Tea): Place 1-2 teaspoons (5-8g) of dried Sensitive Plant herb (leaves, stems) in a teapot or cup. Pour 1 cup (240ml) of boiling water over the herb. Cover and steep for 10-15 minutes. Strain and drink 1-2 cups daily.","For Digestive & Intestinal Support (Traditional Use): Drink 1-2 cups of Sensitive Plant tea daily to traditionally support digestive wellness and intestinal health. Recent traditional use focuses on parasite cleansing and gut health.","For Wound Healing (Topical): Crush fresh Sensitive Plant leaves to release juices and apply directly to minor wounds or skin irritations. The natural astringent properties support wound closure and healing.","Traditional Note: Sensitive Plant (Mimosa pudica) is famous for its leaves that fold when touched. It has been used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine as a powerful healing plant."],"processingMethod":["Selective Harvesting — Herbs are hand-picked at peak maturity, with care to protect plant populations and ecosystems.","Manual Cleaning — Unwanted parts like dirt and dry leaves are removed; useful portions are sorted for quality.","Drying Setup — Delicate herbs are tied in small bunches or spread thinly to allow natural airflow.","Shade Drying — Materials dry slowly in a cool, shaded space to preserve aroma, color, and beneficial properties.","Storage — Once fully dry, herbs are trimmed and sealed in airtight containers to maintain freshness and potency."],"tags":["sensitive plant wildcrafted","mimosa pudica dried","dormilona tea","sensitive plant herbal tea","traditional herb Honduras wildcrafted","sensitive plant traditional uses","sensitive plant relaxation and calm","sensitive plant nervous system wellness","mimosa pudica benefits"],"relatedProducts":["leaf-of-life-miracle-leaf","plantain-leaf","snake-plant","neem-leaves","muicle-herb"],"audience":{"type":"PeopleAudience","suggestedGender":"unisex","suggestedMinAge":13},"disclaimer":"FOR TRADITIONAL USE ONLY. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. Keep out of reach of children. Consult a healthcare professional before use if pregnant or nursing. Individual results may vary."}', '{"handler":"sensitive-plant","productGroupId":"FMT-TH-DO","catalog":"Traditional Herbs","image":{"url":"https://cdn.forestal-mt.com/products/productGroup/sensitive-plant.png","alt":"Sensitive Plan